                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Diverse Elementals",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 142,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The Elemental Planes are more than expanses of sky, rock, metal fire, wood, and ocean. Clouds of fog, dust, and storms float through the Plane of Air. The Plane of Earth includes verdant groves, shining metal and crystal, and irradiated wastelands. The Plane of Fire features magma, suffocating smoke, and radiant firelight. Amid the endless sea of the Plane of Water are pockets of ooze and brine, plus the otherworldly environs of the deep.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "icewyrm",
                "aonid": 666,
                "game-obj": "Monsters",
                "name": "icewyrm",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "firewyrm",
                "aonid": 2983,
                "game-obj": "Monsters",
                "name": "firewyrm",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Elemental Wyrms",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 142,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The icewyrm is the most widely encountered elemental wyrm, but others exist as well, including the blazing firewyrm, the sleek but somewhat smaller sparkwyrm, and the largest of them all, the immense and acidic sludgewyrm.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "silver",
                "aonid": 2920,
                "game-obj": "Equipment",
                "name": "silver",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "dawnsilver",
                "aonid": 2917,
                "game-obj": "Equipment",
                "name": "dawnsilver",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "adamantine",
                "aonid": 2915,
                "game-obj": "Equipment",
                "name": "adamantine",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Looting Earth Elementals",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 142",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 142,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Earth elementals sometimes have valuable gemstones or minerals incorporated into their bodies, and once they\u2019re slain, these valuables can be scavenged as treasure. Gemstones, precious metals such as silver or gold ore, or rarer materials such as dawnsilver or adamantine can be harvested from these creatures, although the more expensive finds tend to be incorporated into only the most powerful earth elementals.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Elemental, Air",
                "aonid": 41,
                "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                "name": "Elemental, Air",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Elemental, Air",
                "aonid": 408,
                "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                "name": "Elemental, Air",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
